Combo Charts
Use a combo chart to display at least two related series of data.
Create a Combo Chart
In the lens, click  and then select the Combo chart type.
In the X-Axis field, add the dimension to analyze the measures by.
In the Y-Axis field, add at least two measures.
To change the chart display, click  and set the chart properties in the Formatting panel.
Create a Combo Chart with Stacked Bars
In a combo chart, you can change the bar to a stacked bar to show and compare parts of a whole.
Click , and then click .
In the dashboard, create a combo chart that shows total opportunity amount as a bar and count of rows as a line, grouped by industry.
Click , and then click .
To filter the sum by Best Case category, click the dropdown next to Sum of Amount, and select Add a Filter.
Select Forecast Category | Best Case, and then click Add.
Create three more instances of the Sum of Amount measure, click the dropdown arrow next to Sum of Amount, and select Clone Column.
Repeat this step two more times so that you have four Sum of Amount measures.
For second, third, and fourth Sum of Amount measures, change the Forecast Category filter to Closed, Commit, and Pipeline, respectively.
To make the measure labels more descriptive, click the dropdown next to the top Sum of Amount measure, and select Edit this Column.
Show the widget properties by clicking .
In the widget properties, expand the Series section, and then click Customize series.
To show all Total measures as bars, select each Total measure in the Measure field and then Bar in the Show As field.
Leave the Count of Rows measure showing as a line.
Under the Combo Chart section, change the Axis Mode to Dual Axis, and select Stack bars to stack all the bars for each industry.
title: Creating Combo Charts in Salesforce Analytics
